    "claim": "After `ACTION_BORROW` or `ACTION_REMOVE_COLLATERAL` sets `status.needsSolvencyCheck = true`, any later unsupported action falls through to the empty `_additionalCookAction()` implementation and overwrites `status` with a zeroed struct. Because `ACTION_ACCRUE` is declared but never handled, a recipe such as `[BORROW, ACCRUE]` or `[REMOVE_COLLATERAL, ACCRUE]` clears the pending solvency check and returns successfully even when the caller is insolvent.",
    "impact": "An attacker can borrow MIM without sufficient collateral or withdraw collateral from an undercollateralized position, leaving the cauldron with immediate bad debt and allowing direct pool drainage.",
    "paths": [
      "Call `cook([5,8], [0,0], [abi.encode(int256(amount), attacker), bytes(\"\")])` to borrow, then clear `needsSolvencyCheck` with the unhandled `ACTION_ACCRUE`.",
      "Call `cook([4,8], [0,0], [abi.encode(int256(share), attacker), bytes(\"\")])` to remove collateral from an already undercollateralized position.",
      "The second action does not need to be `8`; any unsupported action that reaches `_additionalCookAction()` has the same effect in the base contract."
    ]
